{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"36cf27cb-4f54-4fc3-8fa6-a54bc2c3295a","content":"No workflow files found in the repo, so here's a general guide for switching from `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` to **NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC)**:\n\n### 1. Configure NuGet.org\n\nOn [nuget.org](https://nuget.org), go to your package → **Manage** → **Publishing** → **Trusted Publishers** and register a GitHub Actions publisher with:\n- **Repository owner** and **name**\n- **Workflow filename** (e.g. `publish.yml`)\n- **Environment** (e.g. `nuget`)\n\n### 2. Update your workflow\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    environment: nuget            # must match nuget.org config\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write             # required for OIDC token\n      contents: read\n\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n      - uses: actions/setup-dotnet@v4\n        with:\n          dotnet-version: '8.x'\n\n      - run: dotnet pack -c Release\n\n      # Push WITHOUT an API key — trusted publishing uses the OIDC token\n      - name: Publish to NuGet\n        run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg\n          --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n### Key changes\n\n| Before (API key) | After (OIDC) |\n|---|---|\n| `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` in `--api-key` | No `--api-key` flag needed |\n| No special permissions | `permissions: id-token: write` |\n| No environment required | `environment:` must match nuget.org config |\n\n### 3. Clean up\n\n- Remove the `NUGET_API_KEY` secret from your repo/org settings once verified.\n\nThe main idea: NuGet.org verifies the GitHub-issued OIDC token instead of a long-lived API key, so there's no secret to manage or rotate.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"dcd7e53a-0020-4ae5-9f26-39bbee8d7dc8","outputTokens":482,"requestId":"0401:2261B0:A08D00:BAD36D:69F3FB58"},"id":"4d6041ad-b696-483c-9f22-0bbc789fdc44","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:01:23.130Z","parentId":"09494c53-118c-4c31-ab92-eeb54c3ee0a0"}
